Snai Signs Loan Agreement for 490 Million Euros With Three Banks

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-08T23:53:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/snai-signs-loan-agreement-for-490-million-euros-with-three-banks.html
  Snai SpA (SNA)  has signed a loan agreement
of 490 million euros ($681 million), the company said in an e-
mailed statement. The financing arrangement, with  UniCredit SpA (UCG) ,
Banca IMI SpA and Deutsche Bank AG acting as mandated lead
arrangers, is for a medium and long-term loan, divided into
several tranches, of up to a maximum of 490 million euro, the
company said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 